A weathered wooden desk viewed from above, scattered with faded photographs, old airline tickets, and yellowed documents spanning different decades, arranged in a loose spiral pattern suggesting the passage of time. Warm afternoon sunlight streams through a window, casting long shadows across the memorabilia. A single wilting orchid in a small ceramic pot sits at the corner. The color palette is muted sepia tones mixed with tropical greens, evoking both nostalgia and the humid atmosphere of Southeast Asia. Vintage style with soft film grain texture and slightly desaturated colors reminiscent of 1980s photography.
